    "description": "<p>An alternative to the Main Gauche, a parrying dagger has a pair of spring-loaded blades that fan out from the central blade, forming a trident. This weapon is exceptionally good at Bind, getting +1 for this purpose. A Parrying Dagger is only used one-handed, and does [[/r 1d3]] damage, but when attempting to break a sword, it does [[/r 1d6 + 1]] damage; giving it the nickname “Sword-Breaker”.</p>",
